	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>heh, half of you dont know what you're talking about. It's quite funny actually...<br><br>First off, most stats other than wis mean nothing to a druid. All the druid high level equipment is clickable for effects, so you dont need dex. Not like many would pump up dex to proc a heirophants crook anyways. Sta really isnt worth the effort to put up when you can get +hp items. Agi, well agi is just for learning defensive skills mainly, and for some ac. Int if you want to learn trade skills faster. Cha.. well cha is pretty useless. I dont care what you think about the charm animal spells, I'm telling you its stupid. Go charm some bats in sol b... seriously.<br><br>Once you hit the cap of 200 wis, which is pretty easy with high end equipment, you're gonna want to start concentrating on one of a few different options. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp; +AC - To save you a few hp damage.. my outlook on ac is that - as a druid - if you're gonna die, you're gonna die. 100 AC extra isnt gonna save you from the 15 mobs that jumped you cuz invis broke. <br>   +Mana - Mana, ooh mana is so important, oooh ooh.. yeah mana is important, to an extent. You dont need to pump yourself up with it though. A druid can get 13 tick mana regen with his own buffs at level 60. Thats better than C2. With C2 you'll have 24. <br>   + Resists - This is important, switching around sets of armor for diffent dragons can be a pain, especially when its lowering you below 200 wis. Keeping yourself above 200 wis while raising your resists is a very nice thing to be able to do.<br><br>Okay, so I know that this has nothing to do with which class is better. Its just that there was a lot of crap being spewed out in this forum. <br><br>At level 60, there is no 'better class' really. In the beginning, and while leveling up, I guess you might say halfling because of their xp bonus and starting location. Though Wood elves start right by crushbone, where they can make some quick easy plat.<br><br>And one more thing, halflings dont like like 'turds'. Tell me I look like a turd in full ES/vermiculated armor, with a scarab helm on my head, and I'll k33l Y0U! All those woodelves look like fairies anyways, and theres wayyy too many of em.<br><br>Tashin Toadfoot<br>Midnight Sojourn<br>Emarr</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
